{"id":34643,"title":"[Acrodermatitis enteropathica: report of one case].","abstract":"Acrodermatitis enteropathica is an uncommon disease caused by hereditary or acquired zinc deficiency. It is characterized by a triad of alopecia, diarrhea and acral and periorificial dermatitis. It is treated with Zinc supplementation. We report a 31-year-old indigent and drug addict female with a cutaneous-mucous syndrome characteristic of acrodermatitis enteropathica. She had a positive clinical evolution after Zinc supplementation. ","date":"2014-04-10","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24718477","annotations":[{"name":"Disease","weight":0.829843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Diarrhea","weight":0.798641,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diarrhea"},{"name":"Heredity","weight":0.786341,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heredity"},{"name":"Dietary supplement","weight":0.72914,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dietary_supplement"},{"name":"Alopecia","weight":0.643618,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alopecia"},{"name":"Zinc","weight":0.595202,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zinc"},{"name":"Drug","weight":0.576323,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug"},{"name":"Substance dependence","weight":0.51758,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Substance_dependence"},{"name":"Syndrome","weight":0.418173,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syndrome"},{"name":"Dermatitis","weight":0.352404,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dermatitis"},{"name":"Female","weight":0.34328,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Female"},{"name":"Poverty","weight":0.298152,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poverty"},{"name":"Evolution","weight":0.227953,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evolutio